    answer:`1) PHYSIOLOGICAL BASIS:
• Buoyancy unloads weight-bearing joints (~50% in waist-deep water) — reduces compressive forces on arthritic knees/hips
• Hydrostatic pressure: improves circulation, reduces joint swelling
• Viscosity/resistance: natural resistance for strengthening without high joint load
• Result: Cardiorespiratory stimulus achieved WITHOUT joint damage

2) DEPTH ANSWER FOR MARCUS:
• Waist-deep: ~50% body weight unloaded → RECOMMENDED starting point
• Chest-deep: greater energy cost (more buoyancy + more resistance), progress to this
• Knee-deep: least unloading, not ideal for orthopedic relief
• Key point: Energy cost increases markedly with depth — depth IS a progression variable
→ Start waist-deep for safety and pain control; progress to chest-deep over 4–6 weeks

3) 6-WEEK WATER BASE TRAINING:
• Frequency: 3 days/week
• Intensity: Zone 1 (estimate HR ~95–105 bpm; talk comfortably throughout)
