4) PRECAUTIONS:
• Non-slip pool shoes; supervised entry/exit (instability risk)
• Pool temperature 82–86°F (therapeutic for joints; avoid cold = muscle spasm)
• Always warm-up 3–5 min easy water walking before conditioning phase
• Cool-down 3–5 min walking + gentle stretching
• Monitor next-day joint swelling: ice PRN; if persistent = reduce intensity`
  },
  {
    title:"Case 3: Keisha",subtitle:"Talk Test + Anxiety — Cross-Validating Intensity",
    scenario:`Keisha, 35, wants to improve fitness. During submaximal talk test on treadmill:
• 4.5 mph, 3.5% grade → sings effortlessly (RPE 2–3)
• 5.5 mph, 5% grade → short sentences, slight breathlessness (RPE 4)
